# Goose Hints for HTML Editor Monorepo

## Project Overview
This is a monorepo containing:
- `packages/html-editor` - The main HTML editor React library
- `packages/demo-app` - A demo application showcasing the editor
- Shared development tooling and configurations

## Key Files and Directories
- `package.json` - Root package.json with workspace definitions and scripts
- `packages/html-editor/package.json` - Library package configuration
- `packages/demo-app/package.json` - Demo application configuration
- `packages/html-editor/src` - Library source code
- `packages/demo-app/src` - Demo application source code
- `README.md` - Main project documentation
- `CHANGELOG.md` - Version history
- `CONTRIBUTING.md` - Contribution guidelines
- `tests/` - End-to-end tests
- `vitest.config.js` - Unit test configuration
- `playwright.config.js` - E2E test configuration

## Key Scripts
- `npm run build:lib` - Build the HTML editor library
- `npm run dev:demo` - Run the demo application in development mode
- `npm run build:demo` - Build the demo application
- `npm run test` - Run unit tests
- `npm run test:e2e` - Run end-to-end tests
- `npm run lint` - Run linting
- `npm run publish:lib` - Publish the library

## Technologies Used
- React 19+
- prop-types
- Vite (for building)
- Vitest (for unit testing)
- Playwright (for E2E testing)
- ESLint for code quality
- GitHub Actions for CI/CD

## Development Workflow
1. Make changes in `packages/html-editor/src` for library features
2. Test with `npm run test` (unit tests) and `npm run test:e2e` (end-to-end)
3. Preview changes in demo app with `npm run dev:demo`
4. Build with `npm run build:lib` and `npm run build:demo`
5. Publish with `npm run publish:lib`

## Testing
- Unit tests in `packages/html-editor/src/__tests__`
- E2E tests in `tests/` directory
- All tests run with `npm run test` command
- E2E tests run with `npm run test:e2e` command

## Packages Structure
- `packages/html-editor` - Main library export
- `packages/demo-app` - Example application
